Its handy for users to be able to export a space.  Whilst Space Import can be done, this is done by an admin, the password for mail is pretty much useless to 'users', and need not be exposed, and is a security risk (others could POP and grab mail first, causing no end of confusion, which I would like to avoid).

Best case would be to not export it at all in the XML output, or provide a dummy password (accepted, then, that the 'backup' would not result in an 'identical' restore)

An option to 'not' export password information would be great, as only a system admin would do the restore anyway.

